abstract: The last election weakened our democracy. Why aren’t we preparing for the next one?
snippet: The last election weakened our democracy. Why aren’t we preparing for the next one?
lead_paragraph: American democracy has a target on its back: Disinformation has become a firm fixture of political campaigns in the digital age. Given the country’s polarized politics and history of close elections, the prospect that sophisticated influence operations, foreign and domestic, could shape the outcome of the 2020 presidential race is very real — and despite the searing experience of 2016, America is not ready.

abstract: Prime Minister Boris Johnson's promise to take Britain out of the European Union next month could jeopardize a much older union: the United Kingdom which binds together England, Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland.

lead_paragraph: LONDON — Prime Minister Boris Johnson's promise to take Britain out of the European Union next month could jeopardize a much older union: the United Kingdom which binds together England, Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland.

abstract: China commissioned its first domestically built aircraft carrier into service on Tuesday at a key base on the shores of the disputed South China Sea, in another big step in the country's ambitious military modernization.
snippet: China commissioned its first domestically built aircraft carrier into service on Tuesday at a key base on the shores of the disputed South China Sea, in another big step in the country's ambitious military modernization.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — China commissioned its first domestically built aircraft carrier into service on Tuesday at a key base on the shores of the disputed South China Sea, in another big step in the country's ambitious military modernization.

abstract: Cafeteria workers at the debate site enlisted the candidates’ support as they fought successfully for a better contract. The candidates had said they would not cross a picket line to participate.
snippet: Cafeteria workers at the debate site enlisted the candidates’ support as they fought successfully for a better contract. The candidates had said they would not cross a picket line to participate.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — The next Democratic presidential debate will go on as scheduled Thursday, after negotiators on Tuesday reached agreement in a labor dispute that had threatened to upend the event while highlighting organized labor’s influence with the leading Democratic presidential candidates.

abstract: Buoyed by a big new Conservative majority in Parliament, British Prime Minister Boris Johnson toughened his Brexit stance on Tuesday, ruling out any extension of an end-of-2020 deadline to strike a trade deal with the European Union.
snippet: Buoyed by a big new Conservative majority in Parliament, British Prime Minister Boris Johnson toughened his Brexit stance on Tuesday, ruling out any extension of an end-of-2020 deadline to strike a trade deal with the European Union.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Buoyed by a big new Conservative majority in Parliament, British Prime Minister Boris Johnson toughened his Brexit stance on Tuesday, ruling out any extension of an end-of-2020 deadline to strike a trade deal with the European Union.
headline_main: UK's Johnson Seeks to Rule Out Brexit Trade Pact Delay
headline_print_headline: UK's Johnson Seeks to Rule Out Brexit Trade Pact Delay

abstract: Cheap money is driving a property boom that is pricing many residents out of big cities and causing concern among policymakers.
snippet: Cheap money is driving a property boom that is pricing many residents out of big cities and causing concern among policymakers.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — Europe’s economy is struggling to gain traction after years of anemic growth. But the rock-bottom interest rates meant to power a recovery are fueling a property boom that is creating a new set of problems.

abstract: The bungled effort to contain African swine fever could result in higher Chinese food costs for years and shows the limits of Beijing’s top-down approach to problems.
snippet: The bungled effort to contain African swine fever could result in higher Chinese food costs for years and shows the limits of Beijing’s top-down approach to problems.
lead_paragraph: WULONGQIAO, China — A devastating disease spreading from China has wiped out roughly one-quarter of the world’s pigs, reshaping farming and hitting the diets and pocketbooks of consumers around the globe.

abstract: Mr. Gates was hoping to be spared prison. He testified against Paul Manafort and Roger Stone, and prosecutors said he resisted pressure not to cooperate.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Rick Gates, the former Trump campaign aide who helped bring down two former advisers to President Trump, was sentenced on Tuesday to 45 days in jail and a $20,000 fine for his part in a criminal financial scheme and for lying to federal investigators.
